Edopoids include the Late Carboniferous genus Edops and the family Cochleosauridae. Dendrerpetontidae has also been included in Edopoidea, and is the oldest known temnospondyl family. Balanerpeton woodi is the oldest species, having been present over 330 million years ago during the Permian. Dendrerpeton docimus is the most basal known extinct species, restricted to the Rhaetian portion of the Triassic. Their lack of a nasal and lacrimal bone, would strongly suggest a primitive tympanomaxillary articulation or a large contact area between these bones that has not yet evolved toward the modern one.
